description: Investigators say the 39-year-old man from the Paris suburb of Seine-Saint-Denis, who was arrested a week ago, was the fourth and final member of the masked gang that carried out the October 19 robbery on the world's most-visited museum. The stolen jewelry, worth an estimated $102 million, has not been recovered.

headline: The war in Sudan: A tragic symptom of US powerlessness
description: Devastated by the clash between the regular army and the militia led by Mohamed Hamdan Dagalo, known as 'Hemedti,' Sudan has become a battleground for the competing interests of its powerful neighbors – precisely those on whom Donald Trump is relying to end the conflict.

headline: Francis Ford Coppola auctions his watches after  'Megalopolis' disaster
description: The American filmmaker will auction off several collector's items by F.P. Journe, Patek Philippe and Breguet on December 6 and 7, in an attempt to offset the losses from the box-office failure of his latest film.

headline: Leonardo DiCaprio and Paul Thomas Anderson: Two Hollywood stars in Paris after the battle
description: Absent during the European promotion of the film 'One Battle After Another,' the American actor and director reunited in France to talk about Hollywood and their 30-year friendship.

headline: Mexico's new Frida Kahlo museum bends the truth
description: Since opening to the public this fall in Mexico City, a new museum devoted to painter Frida Kahlo has sparked a series of controversies. Contrary to claims by its owners, the house was never the home of the Kahlo family, and a mural discovered on site was likely not the artist's creation.

headline: Jodie Foster: 'Without cinema, I would have been rigid, dry and much more solitary'
description: 'I wouldn't be where I am today if...' In this series, Le Monde interviews a figure about a decisive moment in their life. The American actress pays tribute to her mother, with whom she shared a close, almost inseparable bond for many years.
